Scrambled Eggs Recipe

Ingredients:
4 Eggs
1/4 cup milk
Salt and pepper
2 tsp. butter

Directions:
1. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper in bowl until it's blended
2. Heat butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot.
3. Pour in egg mixture. As eggs begin to se, gently pull the eggs across the pan with a spatula, forming large soft curds.
4. Continue cooking while pulling, lifting and folding the eggs, until it thickens and no visible liquid egg remains. Don't stir constantly. Remove from heat. Serve immediately.